headline: 'We haven't seen the worst of it': Retailers warn tariff impacts are far from over
summary: Tariffs are driving up costs and straining consumers, leaving retailers from Walmart to Best Buy navigating an unpredictable spending environment.

headline: Can Best Buy's Digital Marketplace Expansion Offset Slowing Earnings Growth for BBY?
summary: Best Buy reported its second quarter 2025 earnings, revealing sales of US$9.44 billion and net income of US$186 million, with management maintaining full-year guidance despite lower profits amid softer consumer demand for discretionary electronics. An interesting development is Best Buy's focus on expanding its digital marketplace and repurchasing shares, reflecting an ongoing effort to diversify income streams and reward shareholders even as near-term earnings face pressure.
